      "trait_type": "Method",
      "value": "Instructions:\nPrepare the Shrimp:\n\nFill a large pot with water and bring to a boil.\nAdd the lemon halves and Old Bay seasoning.\nAdd the shrimp and cook for 2-3 minutes, until the shrimp are pink and opaque.\nDrain and transfer the shrimp to a bowl of ice water to cool quickly. Drain again.\n\nMake the Cocktail Sauce:\n\nIn a bowl, combine the ketchup, horseradish, lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce, hot sauce, and salt. Mix well.\n\nAssemble the Platter:\n\nArrange the shrimp on a large platter over a bed of ice.\nGarnish with fresh lemon wedges.\nServe with the cocktail sauce in a small bowl on the side."
